<br>
ter·mi·na·tion   Pronunciation Key  (tûrm-nshn)<br>
1 - The act of terminating or the condition of being terminated. <br>
2- a. The end of something in time; the conclusion. <br>
b. An end of something in space; a limit or edge. <br>
3-A result; an outcome. <br>
4-Linguistics. The end of a word, as a suffix, inflectional ending, or final morpheme<br>
<br>
You automatically assumed termination in the definition refers to the violent ending of existence, however, this is not the case.  Termination is simply the end,  So your following flame and rhetorical question hold no ground.<br>
<br>
____________________________________________________<br>
